Here’s an attempt to scrape SF’s zip code level data posted here. I identified the source link to be this, though not sure yet if this changes over time.

First we prep the list of zipcodes for SF County, using ZCTAs from the Census (which we’ll be able to map as well).

sanfrancisco <- 
  counties("CA",cb=F,progress_bar=F) %>% 
  filter(NAME == "San Francisco")

zctas <-
  zctas(cb=F,progress_bar=F)

sf_zctas <-
  zctas %>% 
  st_centroid() %>% 
  st_join(sanfrancisco,left=F) %>% 
  st_set_geometry(NULL) %>% 
  left_join(zctas, by = "ZCTA5CE10") %>% 
  st_as_sf()

For now I’m opening Developer Tools when viewing the Power BI app and saving the HTML manually (pulling the html directly using rvest won’t work). Need to scroll to the bottom of the list before saving HTML. Will need to switch from rvest to another tool like RSelenium to be able to automate this process.

url <- "sfdatatest.html" # Manual save of HTML data from Power BI through Developer Tools

html <-
  url %>% 
  read_html()

tabledata <- 
  html %>% 
  html_node("[class = 'innerContainer']") %>% 
  xml_child(4) %>% 
  xml_child(1)

date <-
  html %>% 
  html_nodes("svg") %>% 
  html_nodes("text") %>% 
  html_nodes("title") %>% 
  html_text() %>% 
  .[2] %>% 
  substr(12,nchar(.)) %>% 
  as.Date("%m/%d/%Y")

sf_cases <-
  data.frame(
    date = date,
    zipcode = 
      c(
        tabledata %>% 
          xml_child(1) %>% 
          xml_child(1) %>% 
          html_nodes("div") %>% 
          html_text(),
        tabledata %>% 
          xml_child(2) %>% 
          xml_child(1) %>% 
          html_nodes("div") %>% 
          html_text()
      ),
    cases =
      c(
        tabledata %>% 
          xml_child(1) %>% 
          xml_child(3) %>% 
          html_nodes("div") %>% 
          html_text(),
        tabledata %>% 
          xml_child(2) %>% 
          xml_child(3) %>% 
          html_nodes("div") %>% 
          html_text()
      )
  )

saveRDS(sf_cases,paste0("sf_cases_",date,".rds"))

kable(
  sf_cases
)

sf_zctas %>% 
  dplyr::select(zipcode = ZCTA5CE10) %>% 
  left_join(
    sf_cases, 
    by = "zipcode"
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    cases = 
      ifelse(
        cases == "<10",
        NA,
        cases %>% as.character() %>% as.numeric()
      )
  ) %>% 
  mapview(zcol="cases")
